  The Lagos State Government says four COVID-19 patients have been discharged. Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu made this known on Saturday. This brings the number of patients that have recovered and been discharged from the state to 94. He said, “Today, four more persons; three males and one female were discharged to join the society. “The patients; two from the Infectious Disease Hospital, Yaba, and two others from Onikan Isolation Centre, have fully recovered and tested negative twice consecutively to #COVID-19. “This brings the number of patients successfully managed and discharged from our isolation facilities to 94. “Lagos has lost 13 people to #COVID-19. Each person had a unique story and came from a different background.  This brings the number of patients successfully managed and discharged from our isolation facilities to 94.#StayAtHome#TakeResponsibility#LagosAgainstCOVID19  “Today, we mourn them and recommit to doing all we can to slow the spread of #COVID-19. “The risks are real, let’s #StayAtHome and follow guidelines from @LSMOH and @NCDCgov.” Lagos has lost 13 people to #COVID19. Each person had a unique story and came from a different background. Today, we mourn them and recommit to doing all we can to slow the spread of #COVID19. The risks are real, let's #StayAtHome and follow guidelines from @LSMOH and @NCDCgov. 